<Link id="l00619" /><CodeLine lineNumber="619"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00623" /><CodeLine lineNumber="623"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00624" /><CodeLine lineNumber="624"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Transforms a SelectionDAG node and any operands to it into a node</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00625" /><CodeLine lineNumber="625"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// that is compatible with the target instruction selector, as indicated by</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00626" /><CodeLine lineNumber="626"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// the TargetLowering object.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00627" /><CodeLine lineNumber="627"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00628" /><CodeLine lineNumber="628"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// \\returns true if \\c N is a valid, legal node after calling this.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00629" /><CodeLine lineNumber="629"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00630" /><CodeLine lineNumber="630"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// This essentially runs a single recursive walk of the \\c Legalize process</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00631" /><CodeLine lineNumber="631"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// over the given node (and its operands). This can be used to incrementally</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00632" /><CodeLine lineNumber="632"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// legalize the DAG. All of the nodes which are directly replaced,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00633" /><CodeLine lineNumber="633"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// potentially including N, are added to the output parameter \\c</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00634" /><CodeLine lineNumber="634"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// UpdatedNodes so that the delta to the DAG can be understood by the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00635" /><CodeLine lineNumber="635"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// caller.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00636" /><CodeLine lineNumber="636"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00637" /><CodeLine lineNumber="637"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// When this returns false, N has been legalized in a way that make the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00638" /><CodeLine lineNumber="638"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// pointer passed in no longer valid. It may have even been deleted from the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00639" /><CodeLine lineNumber="639"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// DAG, and so it shouldn&#39;t be used further. When this returns true, the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00640" /><CodeLine lineNumber="640"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// N passed in is a legal node, and can be immediately processed as such.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00641" /><CodeLine lineNumber="641"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// This may still have done some work on the DAG, and will still populate</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00642" /><CodeLine lineNumber="642"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// UpdatedNodes with any new nodes replacing those originally in the DAG.</span></CodeLine>
